Vice President Mike Pence met with Chief Executive Dr. Abdullah Abdullah of Afghanistan at the White House to discuss the political environment in Afghanistan. Pence highlighted Abdullah's partnership with Afghan President Ashraf Ghani and the beneficial impact of President Trump's South Asia strategy on the security situation in Afghanistan. Pence commended the bravery and sacrifices of the Afghan security forces in fighting insurgency and international terrorists. He emphasized the need for Kabul's continued engagement and progress on reforms, political inclusion, and preparations for forthcoming elections to provide stability and opportunities for Afghanistan. Pence and Abdullah reaffirmed the enduring partnership between the United States and Afghanistan.